OL,3,CHuman rights groups condemn Rwanda
OL,4,CBill as 'breach of international law'
OL,6,FThe charity Freedom from Torture,
OL,7,Falongside Amnesty International and
OL,8,FLiberty, criticised the Government for
OL,9,Fignoring the findings of the Supreme
OL,10,FCourt, which ruled the policy was
OL,11,Funlawful in November.
OL,13,FThe groups said the Bill poses "a
OL,14,Fsignificant threat to the rule of law"
OL,15,Fby undermining what protects people
OL,16,Ffrom an abuse of power by the state,
OL,17,Fand described Parliament as a "crime
OL,18,Fscene".
